i have been on leave since aug 14. i was sent home from work. i dont know what's gotten into me that i put off resting from an illness due to guilt? i dont know why i feel guilty for getting sick. i've been ill since the whole month of july then i got the dizzy spells.... anemia. i should have known better to have sought consultation early on, but as stubborn as i am, i have to put it off wishing it'll just go away. when it didn't, i have to rush my medical insurance to make sure that i got myself covered. stupid me. 
anyway, my doctor gave me 10 days rest. meaning no calls, no daily hospital rounds and the works. so i think i got more pale since i've been staying indoors for quite sometime now. the farthest that i reached was the gasoline station at the corner where humpy treated me to a graham teddy cinnamon cracker. hehehe....
it's hard to be ill in a froreign land. i dont know why im so afraid fo seeking consult when im surrounded with doctors all day. anyway, those unrealistic fears were put to ease after i had  my first visit to a gyne clinic then onto my internist clinic. those clinics were like a dream... can sure put a patient at ease. 
right now i need to hohummmmm theae iron tablets are making me sleepy

so this is it. this is what it feels like when you're far from everything familiar and home. 
i still can't believe how fast time flies. 
i miss manila so much. the people in my life, the faces and places, the sound, the smell, the sight. everything that is manila.
oh i just feel sooooooo homesick. i miss my parents. my siblings, my friends who make me who i am. 
i cant imagine if i would have gone this far if humpy isn't around. 
bahamas is beautiful but it would be more complete if everybody is here with me.
i hope i can fast track and go home to manila. even for just a while. but not until april... i have something to look forward to.

it's been 3 months since i arrived here, yet no pics posted in my entries. i find it hard to edit the pics and i'm still settling in. 
my humpy is here with me. he arrived a month ago. a presence that decreased the amout of loneliness that i felt missing my family and friends. yes. people are more important than having a fat bank account. well we already know that is not a myth.
take the example of a celeb who just passed away recently and is buried here a couple of days ago... she had money, fame and yet we all know that life hasn't been that good to her as she perceived it. financially it has been. she has problems that she just shrugged off. according to someone who i know knows the couple, the couple are nice people but people and media are just not kind enough. they are so cruel that they camped out in front of the residence with ladder. even in death, she still wasn't given the peace that she deserves... 
maybe im just busy with work and life that i did not bother following the news or paying extra attention to it. what caught my attention is the delay in the memorial services and the last attempt to exhume the son to be taken back to the US. huwaaattttt? even the funeral almost became a circus. i dont want to die like that.

it's been a while lj, i have been to far away place in the philippines and now im off somewhere in the world. i have had beautiful music playing for me for the past year that i irregularly update you. i can't tell if i lived my life in the fast lane that i really don't have much time on my hands then. 
i am here. going over what happened last 2005 i knew the answers. why i wasn't able to leave when i was supposed to or almost about to. now i'm finally here. it's been more than 2 weeks since i left manila. i'm still adjusting here. i left 2 weeks after i had surgery. see... i need to have that done there before leaving...have been putting off consultation since i first had the nosebleed way back august. but it's all done now. the scare was terrible. i'm practically A ok. 
then there was the poea bruhaha... imagine me going to poea in slow mo...like 39 hours post op (GA at that) and then the british airways fiasco... (yoki lounging at the HK int'l airport) hahaha.. i traveled for 24 hours wih 3 plane transfers in 2 huge airports. i can proudly say i survived it all. my life is indeed colorful. 
a week before i left, humpy left too. now we're really miles away from each other. thanks to technology, i still get to see him. i can't wait to have him here soon.
if i have any regrets leaving... hmmmm it was not being able to see or at least talk to some important people before i left...i left hurriedly. i know they will understand.  but vacation is just around the corner... ooopss which reminds me that i need to get my leave schedule for 2007 in on monday! ha!

i was supposed to back to manila as scheduled yesterday by regular trip of the company's private aviation, then the regular flight got cancelled during the last minute. hey... i badly need to go home.. this is the shortest stay i had in the island 28 days... and i want to go back to manila... not only due to superman hahaha.... i spent the entire evening of june 29 trying to catch the last minute booking for a commercial flight. our small plane cessna 402 will fly us to mindoro then i will have to take chance with asian spirit... just to go home. good news is: I MADE IT! im here, sleepless and all. i arrived 8:20 am june 30. i'm just staying at home for now. resting and clearing my mind. it's humpy's birthday tomorrow... the prime reason why i am dying to go home just in time for humpy's birthday. On another note: i am going gaga over this game for the last 24 hours: vampires vs. warewolves.... it's really kinda old news in manila but... what the heck i love this one: come join emaleth

i am so tamad... so pictures under the cut are of different sizes... ah basta post ko lang.... this is ilugao.... isolated and quiet... oh fine sand... stars of ilugao aka guy and pip o vi and bot panian not the pit... on a good friday no operation so alll trucks are resting... sunset... at the pier... cabana beach... ok ok... im soooo tamad....
unfortunately i have only 2.... in this peecee. the rest is in my laptop that i have yet to upload this is tabunan island. private. serene. cool....

im in manila... i miss manila... so im back in cyberspace... the drawback is... i miss my humpy. we won't get to see more of each other as in 24/7 since we're in manila... will post new pics tomorrow. will rest for now

1. oh we all know that i lost my job may 2005 without prior notice that raised the hell within
  2. i was suppossed to go to the Bahamas, then i got bumped off by a cuban national
  3. i accepted the job at Korean Friendship Hospital and it was a-ok
  4. then i went for a temporary LOA and accepted the offer from Semirara Antique and i just wish to try it for a month, that became 6 weeks that furthered into 8 weeks
  5. before i left manila, i registered as a medical practitioner in Queensland
  6. as fate played it's game, i met my humpy in semirara
Semirara is a beautiful place. the perfect peace im looking for. my life took a quiet turn but not that laid back. we are provided with amenities- furnished with free cable TV 2 flr 2 br with bath apt unit, full course meals, endless coffee, drinking water, free electricity that you can leave your aircon day in and day out (oh do this in manila and your bill will be enuf to drive you nuts), there's a tennis court, a badminton court, a gym- without an instructor though. it'll be your choice if you are going to spend. laundry service is a hundred bucks for 1 week. life is simple and stress free. no gasoline prices to worry about. but for mall rats and those who love shopping and movies in wide screen, this is not the place to be. we watched wide screen though, using our laptops and lcd's and our very own living room wall. i was initially accommodated in unit number 39. my eyes widened when i saw the unit. i was looking for a tv when i first arrived there and they provided me with a 21 inch jvc flat tv. o d ba ang babaw... last month before i left for a vacation, i transferred to my newly renovated unit. the wifi is already up so perhaps when i come back there i'll be in lj land once more. i see patients day in and day out 24 hrs a day on call with out-patients during office hours but i'm paid 24/7. the people are nice. and for some of them, humpy and i are the first doctors to have seen them in their entire life. our private hangar sunset at the air strip where we live--- Voin Alpine i live 2nd door to the right-- middle, my permanent accommodation, yes i have the unit all for myself langka tree teeming with fruits within reach in my front yard inside my unit--- renovation going on the stairway the CR re- tiling the floors--- ooops look new ref! my home entertainment cabinet--- now i have an LG flat the tennis court at night, taken from the kiosk where we drink coffee my two chinese neighbors--- tai chi and wu shu instructors--- Ma Hai Tsuin and Sun Won Ting . yes they are imported from china. they don't speak english only mandarin when they arrived and the only person they talk to is my humpy... he is fluent in mandarin, reading, writing, and speaking...i call them tongshingwa... my favorite past time... popping grass pellets taken the day before we left for a vacation, we decided to wear the same uniform sundown at the hospital garage me and my humpy--- valentines day eeekkkk....baduy... sorry no pictures of the oil spill- haven't been to the site myself

lj land... IM BACK!!!! whew! it's like 4 months, i don't know how to begin... so this will do for now...

ohweeehhhhh i was finally able to access the net again so dear lj i'm here. i'll post pictures of this beautiful island the next time i'll have access. 
at this point in time, i feel so confused. i love it here and just as when im feeling i've finally found where i wanna be... my pending applications out of the country are getting clear by the minute and guess what... im bailing out for another year. hahaha so unpredictably me... the one solution i have in mind is: taking it one day at a time :) things will eventually fall into place


ciao:0 miss you lj land

i miss livejournal/ internet access is just so hard here. i miss you guys... :) but it's a beautyiful place to be in... i just love it here

it's a breather to finally write down a word or two...

things got on the run these past few days that i don't update my lj anymore *sigh*, to think i just renewed my account. anyway, i hope i won't be in hiatus for long since i was informed that there is internet access in antique. okay so i'm leaving wednesday for about 4 - 6 weeks, the thought of riding that 9-seater aircraft is what i'm trying to push away. hah hah hah *panics* shew shew shew *slow deep breaths*
i have a lot of things to finish that i have to get them all done before i leave *sighs again* well i consider that a training ground as to how it really feels to be away from everyone i know with no access of going home when i feel like it....

off now.. needed to sign a lot of forms.. the documentation and photocopying stage is done all i need is the courier service and a concrete decision as to where to go once i send those documents by courier..
 a registrar in NICU or back to the basics--- a general practitioner?

due to insomnia and nausea over the current events. i want to rant. i used to be indifferent in political affairs. i just do my job as a law abiding citizen because i feel that is my own small way. i love my country and its inhabitants in my own small way. i may have dream of seeking greener pastures overseas but that does not mean i am turning my back on my roots even if i am only 75% native, my dad is half american. when i was in HS i used to hear my mom say that it doesn't matter who is at the seat of power. what matters is the heart of the one seating in power. look at where it led us so far. everyone who wants to seat himself have their own horrific tales to date and so my homeland is going to the dogs... i can't change the world. i can only make small postive changes in myself hoping to at least unburden my country. simple things like following traffic rules, not spitting on the streets, crossing the pedestrian lane, not littering and being transparent in my transactions are but a few but imagine the impact if one can inspire another to do the same, i guess there is still hope for this country. tang ina tama na ang dada.. lahat gustong umupo kasi lahat gustong mangurakot, if not why are there incidence of violence during baranggay elections? is SK elections worth dying for, considering the amount of stipend you are to receive from the government? corruption is not only measured in terms of gold. korea is also a corrupt country, but the koreans love their nation so much that they did their share in their own small way and never failed to pray for their country.. look at where they are now. we may live in a banana republic, with a bogus president, who by her public apology silently shouted at the nation: hey I can't be trusted! now we are the laughing stock of the world. look at us: alila na ng mundo, where teachers and engineers go abroad to work as domestic helpers with the exception of a few (feeling pushed against the wall) and where doctors become nurses... tsk tsk... this is the sad fate of my nation, sad but true, where most of my country men care more about the I. I want this. I want that. puro pakabig, parang laging nagmamahjong. I pity the countless men and women who died for this country, and i guess they are quite ready to bolt out of their graves. what we really need is a change of heart... a change within, even before attempting to change thy husband, wife, brother, sister family, friends, neighbors and countrymen, take a closer look at the man in the mirror.

so i was finally able to visit the clinic of jo and jaybee in the new medical city. wow... it really looks great. modern contemporary, simply fabulous. i just love the interiors. jaybee has such modern hi tech medical equipments. grabe! jo was still herself, and just by looking at her, i can tell she is happy. they are happy :) she has lots of patients na. i am happy to see my classmates living the life cut out for them. who would ever think that 11 years ago, that vacant lot beside the place where we received our degree will turn out to be that place...
so what are you waiting for? there's a good opthalmologist who i entrusted to check my sister and a good pediatrician along meralco avenue. MAB room 612.

i am so tired... yesterday, i went on duty at Korean Philippines Friendship Hospital. i just want to have a feel of everything once more. so i had my first taste of it. the first after 4 years. oh i just have to watch over the patients and manage them ~ simple cases that i often meet~asthma, dengue, typhoid to name a few.... no ER. just a couple of admissions that's it. what made me tired is catching newborns in the delivery room. wow i had a hand at it after 4 years. after training, i used to have my babies catched by a resident and i just get notified by phone, then i do my rounds. now i catch them once more. for starters, i had 2 premature neonates, one at 36-37 weeks, feeding well, no problems weighing 2.3 kgs. the toxic one was a 30-31 weeker weighing 1.82 kgs and in respiratory distress. perhaps that kid is intubated by now. the brain work and the hyphe was what i missed. the exhaustion... hmmm i don't think so. anyway, this is just temporary, after getting bored with managing simple cough and colds and some malingering patients, i just wanna have a feel of it once more.

when i got your message this morning and i did not respond, it was a deliberate action. you never noticed anything when you gave me a call, i was still myself. the voice, the laughter, the person whom you draw your strength from these past few weeks or was it months now? i dare not show you that i am also weak. that i am emotionally and psychologically weak. when i decided to meet up with you, at the back of mind, i was thinking that this might be the last before i go on temporary hibernation. please prove to me that i am wrong. that i am just overreacting and that i just got all things mixed up. i feel sorry that i read you wrongfully. i refuse to look at the glaring fact that you just need company and i'm the one who accidentally happens to be here. i'm sorry...
why did you try avoiding the topic that i was about to ask you. too bad, you are not good at it. you haven't learned that much from me. the perfection of the harry houdini escape. i wanted to hear it straight from you so that i can set my emotions straight and back on tract. if in case you don't know, it'll set me free. instead your avoidance made my heart feel so sad. you can just casually answer my question as to how your day went and who you were with. it was just a normal conversation that we always have. what confuses me is the same issue we had in the past... you tell me everything. your deepest secrets in life, your burdens and yet i'm always the last to know when you are seeing someone else and/or planning to. it is not as if you don't have the right. by all means... you have it and i won't take it away from you. the moment you ended the call i just don't feel like being confrontational now. so i write. i write it all here... because i know you don't know and will never know. do you even have the slightest idea that livejournal exists and that i write almost always regularly? because if you do, i think i don't need to talk to you anymore. it's all here hence saving me the trouble...

Your Aries Drinking Style
Impulsive Aries people like to party and sometimes don't know when to call it a night. Your competitive streak makes you prone to closing time shot contests. You're a sloppy, fun drunk, and you get mighty flirty after a couple tipples. Getting you drunk is a good way for people to get what they want out of you, should other methods fail. You can become bellicose when blotto, but you will assume that whatever happened should be forgiven (if not forgotten) by sunrise. You can be counted on to do the same for others -- so long as they haven't gone and done anything really horrible to you last night (ahem, sneaky Gemini!)
Your Signature Cocktails
Aries, born under the hot-stuff planet Mars, is the ruler of spicy food and red things -- and for balance, astrologers recommend they eat tomatoes, onions, olives and greens. That's right, Aries, you were born under the sign of the bloody Mary. Aries also rules grapefruit, and they've been known to kick back a salty dog and a sea breeze or two. For extreme hotcha, try a concoction with cinnamon liqueur in it.

only this time, i regret that you won't find me. i will deliberately disappear. this is too much. or am i overreacting? the first time should have been a lesson and i should have learned it well. unfortunately, i allowed a "second time around" thing, that i was thinking i could handle if things get tough once more. that i am in total control of things and emotions unlike before. it seems kinda unfair for you because you never had the chance to hear it from me directly. i was about to but due to some interruptions, i wasn't able to then i chose not to disclose any nor to give you any clues (did i?) i know i should've told you during one of our conversations but i just chickened out because you caught me unaware and i was pushed to the wall. that happens when i feel i can't control the flow of a conversation. i hide. i put on a mask. the topic made me queasy. so i laughed to lighten up the atmosphere between the two of us. this is how i am. you should've have known, that i have the tendency to clam up. was i a very good and credible actress that i was able to convince you by just nodding and smiling? just like before and you never knew what went on inside this crazy grey matter of mine. please don't say sorry this time. it wasn't your fault that i found myself falling for you once again... so the most i can do is to run away... i am lost. let's just wait for the day when i regain total control of myself that i can't get affected by whatever you do or how you treat me. i still have to get over my tendency to misinterpret your actions...
this journal is where i will write it. you never need to know. i just have to ventilate and calm my waters that you disturbed once more...
i have a new lay out... though i'm caught between the harry potter lay out and lotus lily, i decided this layout has more calming effect :)

The way I see it, if you want the rainbow, you gotta put up with the rain. ---Dolly Parton yesterday i met with . seeing her just feels so heartwarming. knowing seeing friends who are doing well in their lives makes me feel so happy. it uplifts my spirits... d ba ? i went to the library. library as in library and not the one in malate. i am moving on from where it all started. picking up the pieces i tried avoiding. staying in the library gives me anxiety so i avoided going there as much as possible. using medline gives me the creeps. this caused my neglect of the necessary things. little things yet necessary. after 4 years of pretending libraries don't exist and ovid and herdin suck, i went in. started searching medline... and re starting my life back on tract.... the reason is simple: i just want the library all to myself just like the old days when the library is just for the few who really wants to read and research and not chitchat..

last night was one of my darkest moments. but it was not new to me anymore. i can't remember the countless times i fell prey to the dark creatures who disguised themselves as humans. my job item got snatched at the last minute when i was almost due to ship my belongings (err food items). of course i cried buckets and buckets of tears. i was informed thru ym chat that a cuban doctor teacher, not even a pediatrician (here they go again), who happens to be a wife of a bahamian national, took my slot. the switch happened so fast that the doctors who were in charge of transporting and accommodating me there got shocked. well that's life it's not our territory. now i have to wait until november. i can only feel the hurt because this is not the first time. memories came flooding in...years ago in one of the hospitals in manila while i was applying for residency in the dept of obstetrics and gynecology, i ranked number two. when they called for pre residents (8 in number) my slot got snagged by another doctor, who i never saw during the exams nor during the interview. i can't miss her because i know her and we are chika. the reason was plain and simple: among us applicants, i was the only one without a backer who moved her finger because she found out i topped the exams. she was confident that i will not be dislodged from the ranks even if they get 3. that was a sure slot. see, they called for 8, i wasn't there. because of this i gave up my dream of becoming an obstetrician and applying in manila. those were tough times when doctors are still doctors and not sporting nurse's caps. the incident paved the way for what i was planned to be: a pediatrician. come to think of it, i am aware i'm better off being in pediatrics because i just take it with a grain of salt. in ob, i have a hard time doing hand tying skills. haha... it was meant to be. i will not seek the answers for what happened for i know they will come in due time when all is set and i will finally be able to put all the pieces of my puzzle together. this won't stop me. i will just have to wait a few more months because the cuban can't wait. just this morning i called to confirm our slot in an office in makati to work temporarily as a medical evaluator, because we are due to report tomorrow... would it be surprising to know that it got snagged last friday... well at least there was one slot and i gave it to someone special who needs it more than i do... but it seems i didn't get enough beating... as i was traversing diosdado macapagal avenue on the way to help my dad who will be doing lipat-bahay for my nurse friend, cielo, (that's another story: she was almost hog-tied massacared last thursday)... a huge billboard fell in front of me, missing my car by the hair. yes, BILLBOARD! it was the billboard of Hobbies of Asia, with the chicken wire fence falling with it. and of all cars... my car and with me driving. what are the chances of having a billboard crashing down on you... imagine the horror in front of me,seeing the huge crashing billboard. i thought it fell on my windshield. i swerved to the left but my front tire ran over the steel supports causing my right front tire to burst and on close inspection, even my mag wheels got pierced to the center.... how lucky can i get. i'm just too tired to write. YEP... THIS PIERCED MY TIRE AND MAGS... AND MY MUFFLER AS WELL... everything in less than 24 hours... iba ka pag yoki ang name mo... bugbog sarado hey can anyone see a huge "HIT ME!" SIGN ON MY FOREHEAD... i might have missed reading it, or was it written somewhere on my back... whew--- life...

i dreamt of you last night and i woke up crying. i guess i just miss you a lot and was just trying to keep my mind off things. as in everything. most of the time im in front of the pc playing ragnarok, day in day out for the last 6 days. it's been like 10 months since i last saw you. never bother writing letters to you anymore because i don't know what to say to a person who i miss so much. and besides, what else am i gonna do, rant and ramble? that's what my life is like right now so i suddenly clam up, lick my wounds until i'm ready to face the world again, stronger than ever, ready to let hell break loose. i am also waiting for the time to wish well the people who did me wrong and hurt me so much. i don't talk to people around me that much anymore, they too have their problems and battles. i am living a secluded life at home, with my pc, with my ragnarok--- this is what i do catharsis and waste of ceiling high electricity costs...

wow! it's june. a couple of weeks ago, i got a ragnarok installer cd from one of the sponsors of pepot. because i got so bored, i decided to give it a try... now i'm addicted to playing it... second childhood? the game became my outlet. it made me avoid ranting on my lj temporarily regarding the recent incident from where i work. i want to channel all the negative energies the people "who i thought were my friends" gave me. 
yep. i finally got the letter. i got the formal letter last sunday. save them from hell breaking loose. but the date of the letter says it all. of course i sent a very sarcastic text message to the unethical people... something that goes---"mabuti naman at hindi nyo pinangatawanang bastos kayo.... blah, blah, blah" 
come to think of it. these people don't even deserve me at all. i will not tell them to talk to the hand because they don't even deserve the finger. i just have to let it all out. how can one even continue to work with all the back stabbers who are professionals at that? the good thing is--- it didn't make me lesser of a person. 
i will just play ragnarok and eventually, my rage will lessen until i will have to wish them well. for now i shut up and hope this school year will bring hell to those who deserve it. read: talk about wishing them well, im still enraged.
